collections.name: Aura of Everyday
collections.description:
The extraordinary hides in plain sight.

Aura of Everyday is a photographic exploration of subtle beauty — fleeting moments, quiet textures, and light that falls just right.

Each image captures a fragment of the ordinary: a curve in the road, the echo of geometry in a shadow.

Through composition and stillness, these photographs reflect the invisible atmosphere that surrounds our daily lives — the aura we rarely notice, but always feel.

Shot across the landscapes and urban silence, this series invites you to look again — and then, to feel.

Aura of Everyday.

collections.name: Flora Obscura
collections.description:
There’s something alluring about a hidden beauty. But what if the mask itself held the charm? In “Flora Obscura,” Orangehare mainstay Klara teams up with Korean tattoo artist Sam I Am Green to deliver 47 unique one-of-one portraits. Known for delicate botanical tattoo sketches, Sam submits work from a place where tattoos remain taboo, if not outright illegal. That quiet defiance finds a natural partner in Klara’s meditative focus on feminine grace. Brought to life through Orangehare’s in-house production process, these works move beyond skin-deep toward a celebration of beauty marked, masked, and sometimes, seen clearer.
Instagram: @orangehare.io
Twitter: @Orangehare_io
